claim.claim-text:
1. An elevator system comprising: 
an elevator shaft; 
a linear motor primary element mounted in the shaft; 
a source of substantially constant frequency alternating current electrically connected to the linear motor primary element; 
a plurality of cars residing in the shaft; 
a variable speed elevator car linear drive motor apparatus mounted to each car, the variable speed elevator car linear drive motor apparatus comprising: 
a linear motor secondary element affixed to each car, the secondary element electromagnetically coupled with the primary element; 
a run contract electrically connected in series with the secondary element; and 
a linear motor control apparatus wired in series with the secondary element and the run contact, the linear motor control apparatus comprising: 
(i) an electronic speed control device; and 
(ii) a resistor electrically connected in parallel with the speed control device.
